# AI SDK Core: Overview

AI SDK 6 is now available.

## AI SDK Core

Large Language Models (LLMs) are advanced programs that can understand, create, and engage with human language on a large scale.

AI SDK Core simplifies working with LLMs by offering a standardized way of integrating them into your app.

## AI SDK Core Functions

### generateText
Generates text and tool calls. This function is ideal for non-interactive use cases such as automation tasks where you need to write text (e.g. drafting email or summarizing web pages) and for agents that use tools.

### streamText
Stream text and tool calls. You can use the streamText function for interactive use cases such as chat bots and content streaming.

Both generateText and streamText support structured output via the output property (e.g. Output.object(), Output.array()), allowing you to generate typed, schema-validated data for information extraction, synthetic data generation, classification tasks, and streaming generated UIs.

## Best Practices from Documentation:
1. Use generateText for non-interactive tasks
2. Use streamText for chat/interactive use cases
3. Use structured output for type validation
4. Handle errors properly from AI responses

## Error Handling
- All AI SDK functions may throw errors
- Use try-catch for API calls
- Handle streaming errors with proper cleanup

## Version: AI SDK 6.x
Source: https://sdk.vercel.ai/docs/ai-sdk-core/overview
